Ladysmith Black Mambazo founder Joseph Shabalala died on Tuesday morning in a Pretoria hospital. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has declared a special official funeral for Joseph Shabalala. The founder of Ladysmith Black Mambazo died last week Tuesday at the age of 78. READ: Joseph Shabalala's family announces date for funeral The funeral will take place on Saturday. Ramaphosa has ordered that the national flag be flown at half-mast at every flag station in the country until Saturday evening.